---
---

<section id="philosophy" class="si-section si-philosophy-section">
  <div class="si-container">
    <div class="si-section-header si-reveal">
      <span class="si-section-num">09 / 10</span>
      <h2 class="si-section-title">Security Philosophy</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="si-philosophy-grid">

      <div class="si-phil-statement si-reveal">
        <div class="si-phil-num">01</div>
        <div class="si-phil-body">
          <p class="si-phil-text">Visibility is the foundation of defense.</p>
          <p class="si-phil-sub">
            You cannot protect what you cannot observe. Before any hardening, 
            comprehensive logging and telemetry must exist. Blind spots are 
            where incidents live undetected.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="si-phil-statement si-reveal">
        <div class="si-phil-num">02</div>
        <div class="si-phil-body">
          <p class="si-phil-text">Systems become safer when deeply understood.</p>
          <p class="si-phil-sub">
            Surface-level security is cosmetic. True defensive posture 
            emerges from understanding how each component behaves, where 
            assumptions are made, and where those assumptions break.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="si-phil-statement si-reveal">
        <div class="si-phil-num">03</div>
        <div class="si-phil-body">
          <p class="si-phil-text">Curiosity is one of the strongest defensive tools.</p>
          <p class="si-phil-sub">
            Every unusual log entry is a question. Every unexpected behavior 
            is an invitation to understand. The investigative mindset — not 
            the reactive one — builds resilient infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="si-phil-statement si-reveal">
        <div class="si-phil-num">04</div>
        <div class="si-phil-body">
          <p class="si-phil-text">Defense is a discipline of reduction.</p>
          <p class="si-phil-sub">
            Every open port, every exposed version string, every unnecessary 
            permission is attack surface. Good security is about making deliberate 
            choices to minimize what exists to be targeted.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="si-phil-statement si-reveal">
        <div class="si-phil-num">05</div>
        <div class="si-phil-body">
          <p class="si-phil-text">Assume breach. Design for containment.</p>
          <p class="si-phil-sub">
            No perimeter holds indefinitely. Architectures that assume perfect 
            prevention fail completely when that assumption breaks. Layer defenses 
            so that a single failure cannot cascade into total compromise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="si-phil-statement si-reveal">
        <div class="si-phil-num">06</div>
        <div class="si-phil-body">
          <p class="si-phil-text">Security and velocity are not opposites.</p>
          <p class="si-phil-sub">
            The engineering teams that move fastest are often the ones 
            that invested in security tooling and culture early. Friction 
            comes from fear of the unknown — transparency eliminates it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Hidden element - easter egg -->
    <div class="si-classified si-reveal" id="si-classified">
      <div class="si-classified-bar">
        <span class="si-classified-label">CLASSIFIED · SECTION 10</span>
        <button class="si-classified-toggle" id="si-classified-toggle">
          [ REVEAL ]
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="si-classified-content" id="si-classified-content" style="display:none;">
        <div class="si-classified-inner">
          <div class="si-hidden-header">
            <span class="si-hidden-tag">INTERNAL USE ONLY</span>
            <span class="si-hidden-id">LOG-OMEGA-7 · CLEARANCE REQUIRED</span>
          </div>
          <p class="si-hidden-text">
            The most dangerous vulnerability in any system is not a misconfgured header 
            or an absent rate limit. It is the assumption that observation ends where 
            documentation does. Every undocumented behavior is potential attack surface.
          </p>
          <div class="si-hidden-entry">
            <span class="si-hidden-key">Hidden node:</span>
            <span class="si-hidden-val">internal.observatory.sec:9000 — not in topology map</span>
          </div>
          <div class="si-hidden-entry">
            <span class="si-hidden-key">Classified log:</span>
            <span class="si-hidden-val">omega_7_recon.log — access requires elevated clearance</span>
          </div>
          <div class="si-hidden-entry">
            <span class="si-hidden-key">Command:</span>
            <span class="si-hidden-val">Try typing <code class="si-inline-code-dark">whoami --clearance</code> in the terminal.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="si-hidden-footer">
            ◈ You found the hidden section. Curiosity acknowledged.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .si-philosophy-section {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #070b14 0%, #0a0f1e 100%);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.06);
  }

  .si-philosophy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.08);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .si-philosophy-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .si-philosophy-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .si-phil-statement {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    padding: 36px 28px;
    border-right: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.06);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.06);
    transition: background 0.3s;
  }

  .si-phil-statement:hover {
    background: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.03);
  }

  .si-phil-num {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.2);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 3px;
  }

  .si-phil-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .si-phil-text {
    font-family: 'Syne', 'Playfair Display', sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: rgba(200, 220, 240, 0.82);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .si-phil-sub {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(180, 200, 220, 0.4);
  }

  /* Classified */
  .si-classified {
    border: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.15);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(7, 11, 20, 0.8);
  }

  .si-classified-bar {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    background: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.04);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.1);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .si-classified-label {
    color: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.5);
  }

  .si-classified-toggle {
    background: none;
    border: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.2);
    color: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.65);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .si-classified-toggle:hover {
    background: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.08);
    color: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.9);
  }

  .si-classified-content {
    animation: si-reveal-content 0.4s ease forwards;
  }

  .si-classified-inner {
    padding: 24px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .si-hidden-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .si-hidden-tag {
    color: rgba(220, 90, 90, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(220, 90, 90, 0.2);
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .si-hidden-id {
    color: rgba(180, 200, 220, 0.3);
  }

  .si-hidden-text {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(180, 200, 220, 0.5);
    font-style: italic;
    padding: 14px;
    border-left: 2px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.15);
    background: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.03);
  }

  .si-hidden-entry {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .si-hidden-key { color: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.5); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .si-hidden-val { color: rgba(180, 200, 220, 0.55); }

  .si-inline-code-dark {
    color: rgba(100, 210, 140, 0.75);
    background: rgba(100, 210, 140, 0.07);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .si-hidden-footer {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.4);
    padding-top: 8px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(71, 193, 226, 0.06);
    text-align: center;
  }

  @keyframes si-reveal-content {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-8px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const toggle = document.getElementById('si-classified-toggle');
  const content = document.getElementById('si-classified-content');
  let revealed = false;

  toggle?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    revealed = !revealed;
    if (content) content.style.display = revealed ? 'block' : 'none';
    if (toggle) toggle.textContent = revealed ? '[ CONCEAL ]' : '[ REVEAL ]';
  });
</script>
